        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Cullman, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Baileyton, Cullman, Baldwin, Hulaco, Cole Springs, Battleground, Eva,
Lacon, Holly Pond, and Vinemont.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
north central and northeastern Alabama.</instruction>
